rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Make XML parser more tolerant.
Include some test cases as part of the installation.
Test Suite tests are failing on systems that don't have RDF::Query; make these tests optional.
Support case-sensitive/-insensitive prefixes on a prefix-by-prefix basis rather than parser-by-parser.
@profile properly supports multiple URIs.
Allow an LWP::UserAgent to be supplied when configuring the parser.
Remove 'my' from a couple of lines.
Improved DataRSS support; differentiate between DataRSS and plain Atom.
Handle <?profile ?> processing instructions.
Hard-coded the Yahoo SearchMonkey profile.
Allow Config.pm to provide a list of default profiles to the parser.
UTF-8 fixes necessitating requiring a newer version of RDF::Trine.
Various media-type handling clean-ups.
Auto-Config fixes and clean-ups.
Rearrange some of the documentation in the FEATURES section.
Support for OpenDocument's slightly unusual flavour of RDFa.
Fix broken support for XML literals.
Various clean-ups.
Generate less-predictable blank node identifiers.
Add test cases covering @profile.
Support rdfa:vocabulary in Profiles.
If @graph support is enabled, and RDFa attributes are being used in a non-standard namespace, assume @graph is in that namespace too.
RDFa Profiles establish both a case-sensitive and case-insensitive term mapping.
Strongly deprecate keyword_bundles config option - use default_profiles instead.
Reimplement RDFa 1.0 keyword concept using profiles.
There was an inconsistency between the code and documentation for the name of the oncurie/ontoken callback. It's now called ontoken.
Support for KjetilK's named graph idea.
Load Profile modules via Module::Pluggable.
The final prefix defined in @prefix was being ignored due to a regexp bug. Fixed.
new_from_url didn't work when called without a Config object.
Second parameter to ontriple callback is now a hashref of elements rather than just the current element - this change is to help support the RDFa API.
Deprecated pretriple_literal and pretriple_resource callbacks - use ontriple instead.
@graph is now parsed like @about by default.
Use official GRDDL profile URI for hard-coded support for GRDDL keywords instead of previously used internal identifier.
Fix failure parsing embedded RDF/XML with blank nodes.
Improve HTTP caching behaviour.
More test cases, including XML Literals and named graphs.
Change cache directory.
Support @cite - not part of RDFa, but often provides useful information.
Support @longdesc - not part of RDFa, but often provides useful information.
IETF link types now use an aggressively cached copy of http://www.iana.org/assignments/link-relations/link-relations.xml.

Clarify language around default prefix versus default vocabulary (or in RDFa 1.0 default prefix versus 'no prefix'). This involved renaming a couple of configuration options: prefix_default => vocab_default; prefix_empty => prefix_default.
Improve documentation and include it inline in the module code.
Make named graphs handling more predictable for triples spread across multiple elements.
The graph() and graphs() methods now return RDF::Trine::Model objects.
Fix bug in Turtle output.
Allow various parsing options to be passed to constructor.
Support for @prefix now optional, off by default.
Support for @lang now optional, off by default.
Support for extended @rel/@rev now optional, off by default.
Support for HEAD, BODY and BASE elements now optional, on by default.
Support for full URIs instead of CURIEs now optional, off by default.
Add optional support for xml:base.
Add optional support for embedded RDF/XML.
Add optional support for XFN 1.1 keywords.
Diallow Safe CURIEs in @src/@href.
Disable thing-described-by.org URIs by default.
Module SVN repository now at <http://goddamn.co.uk/viewvc/perlmods/>
Use RDF::Trine::Node::Literal::XML if it exists.
Various test case compliance fixes (passes XHTML test suite).
Various test case compliance fixes (passes HTML4 and HTML5 test suites)
Flexible keyword extensibility (optional).
Special rel='alternate stylesheet' handling (optional, good for HTML5).
Allow suffix-less CURIEs without colons (optional).
Allow case-insensitive CURIE prefixes (optional, good for HTML).

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: I can no longer remember what this patch did!
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Add KjetilK's patch.
Empty CURIE prefix can be configured (optional).
Add Auto Config feature.
Make xml:lang support optional (enabled by default).
Special support for RDFa in Atom (Yahoo's weirdly-named 'DataRSS').
Add support for a default prefix (different from empty prefix).
Include a catalogue of doctypes to speed up XML parsing.
Upgrade distribution to my new packaging regime (signatures, auto-generated changelogs, etc)
Copyright 2010.
Change set_callbacks parameters and support additional callbacks.
Improve named graph documentation.
Correct name of XML::Atom::OWL module in POD.
Document auto-config in non-XHTML XML.
&set_callbacks no longer supports old argument syntax.
&named_graphs no longer supported as a way to enable named graph support.
Fix double use of &consume in POD SYNOPSIS.
POD NAME section short description to match description in CPAN registered modules list.
Bugfix for @property.
Arrange methods in a more sensible order for documentation.
Document HTML support better.
Document Atom support better.
Document SVG support better.
Document RDF/XML support better.
Release RDF::RDFa::Parser 1.00 and RDF::RDFa::Parser::Redland 1.00.
Don't use in plain literal stringification.
Properly enforce scoping of prefix mappings (use Storable qw/dclone/).
Don't use in plain literal stringification.
Properly enforce scoping of prefix mappings (use Storable qw/dclone/).
Change syntax of @prefix to match current RDFa 1.1 editors' drafts.
Support @vocab attribute to set default attribute.
Support @profile attribute to load externally-defined keywords and terms.
Refactor a lot of code, especially CURIE processing.
Broke support for CURIEs with zero-length suffxes.
Rewrite callback stuff.
Fix packaging problem (profile modules were not in MANIFEST).
Refactor error handling code to add a new 'onerror' callback, and an 'errors' method to get a list of errors.
New 'oncurie' callback.
Deprecate OPTS_XXXX functions in favour of a new RDF::RDFa::Parser::Config object which allows host languages and RDFa versions to be combined more flexibly.
Allow CURIEs to have zero-length suffixes.
Broke auto_config.
Support @role attribute.
Use latest list of IANA terms from draft-nottingham-http-link-header-09.txt.
Provide graph() method to output graph.
Fix auto_config.
Provide more inclusive XML DTD catalogue.
Integrate official RDFa test suite into module tests.
new_from_url shortcut.
Special Open Graph Protocol support.
Makefile.PL doesn't reflect proper requirements from running tests.
Tests require File::Slurp. Add this dep to Makefile.PL.
